Calculate RMSE

RMSE.Rd

Root Mean Square Error (RMSE) = standard deviation of the residuals (prediction errors).

RMSE(m, o)

Arguments

m

predicted value (fitted by modelling)
o

oserved 'true' value

Value

numeric value

Examples

library(dplyr)

#> 
#> Attache Paket: 'dplyr'
#> The following objects are masked from 'package:stats':
#> 
#>     filter, lag
#> The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
#> 
#>     intersect, setdiff, setequal, union
library(tidyr)

pred_data  <- predict_votes(c("Eidg1","Kant1"), votedata, exclude_votes=TRUE)

pred_data %>%
drop_na() %>%
group_by(vorlage) %>%
summarize(rmse=RMSE(pred,real))
